Assuming you are referring to the new version:

- Make sure you've updated to the latest version, B000016; this issue may be caused by a bug that was caught in that update.

- If that doesn't work, or your app was already up to date, try setting your wallpaper to something else, then setting it back to Clock Studio, and then open the settings app.

replyContent:
Thanks for the 5 stars, the great review... and the chuckle :)
Although I can't promise anything, I will seriously consider your suggestion, and experiment with removing the icon. I actually rather liked having speedy, home screen access. to the settings utility.
Anyways, time will tell.
Cheers,

LW
